Hier ist gerade jemand, der meinen Küchenboden repariert. Und ich tu jetzt so, als hätte ich noch einen Job und würde von zu Hause aus arbeiten, während ich an Too Hot to Handle sitze.
If I could just damn manage to open the file. (Damn One Drive.)
*Voice of a Hacker* I'm in.
And that's exactly when he starts drilling super loudly. Yay.
It feels uncomfortably passive-aggressive to crank my air purifier to the max, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would even be completely okay, even if he wasn't a mask opponent. And do I really need to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't until he's gone.
At least I finally finished revising Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damn terrifying. Oh yeah, this is the good stuff!
I'm doing Find and Replace for … ➡️ Ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I'm sticking to it. Natural language is usually choppy, especially when you get emotional.
The handyman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully that means he's about to finish.
He went out to cut something (it sounds like that, at least). I sneaked a peek to see how far he is. There's still a lot to do :(
Still 7 pages in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's quite orderly – mainly changes to the font and very small corrections in direct speech, and I need to make everything a bit more concise. But I really could use a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
He just started vacuuming again. Hopefully that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me that he had made a cost estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were cheap and only paid for the part next to the door that is no longer in order. Feels much better now.
The house is being ventilated and in the kitchen my air purifier is running while I'm drinking tea in the garden!
